Feature: Place Order
  Scenario: Orders should be sorted by the number of seconds they are in the queue
    Given I am regular customer with client ID "1001"
    When I place an order with "10" donuts
    Then I see order "1" created successfully for client ID "1001"
    Given I am regular customer with client ID "1002"
    When I place an order with "20" donuts
    Then I see order "2" created successfully for client ID "1002"
    And I see order are sorted by the number of seconds

Scenario: Orders from premium customers always have a higher priority than orders from regular customers
Given I am regular customer with client ID "1001"
When I place an order with "10" donuts
Then I see order "1" created successfully for client ID "1001"
Given I am premium customer with client ID "999"
When I place an order with "20" donuts
Then I see order "2" created successfully for client ID "999"
And I see order from premium customers is given higher priority

Scenario: Client should be able to check the queue position and wait time
Given I am "Regular" client having order in the queue
Then I see my order position in the queue along with wait time
And Wait time should change based on orders in the queue

Scenario:Manager should be able to see all entries in the queue with the approximate wait time
Given There are multiple order in the queue
When Manager check for entries in the queue
Then All the entries in the queue are listed along with wait time